sql:
SELECT gender, value
FROM gender_data
WHERE gender = 'Female';

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_value
FROM gender_data
WHERE indicator_id = 1 AND gender = 'Female';

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_health_indicator_value
FROM gender_data
WHERE gender = 'Male';

SELECT AVG(population) AS average_population
FROM population_data
WHERE year_id = (SELECT year_id FROM years WHERE year_name = 2010);

SELECT policy_name, budget
FROM health_policies
WHERE budget = (SELECT MIN(budget) FROM health_policies);

external_knowledge:
- Available data refers to country data with non-NULL average health indicator values; 
- The query covers multiple years and genders; 
- It includes all countries, regardless of the presence of a health policy for a given year; 
- Health indicators and policies are assumed to be relevant to understanding the health situations and government actions across different countries over time.
